This paper discusses the evolution of local features in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with image and video analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses machine learning and deep learning methods, which are relevant to subcategories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper's focus on 3D reconstruction also suggests relevance to cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the mention of benchmarks and evaluations suggests relevance to cs.MM (Multimedia).
